\section{Introduction}
The AML (Advanced Mathematical Logic) package provides a set of custom symbols for logic operations, which are useful for typesetting complex mathematical expressions. The package defines the following symbols:

\begin{itemize}
    \item $\ifL$ - The custom "if" symbol
    \item $\elseL$ - The custom "else" symbol
    \item $\elifL$ - The custom "else if" symbol
    \item $\toL$ - The custom "to" symbol
    \item $\alsoL$ - The custom "also" symbol
    \item $\additionalcontent$ - The custom "additional content" symbol
    \item $\doneL$ - The custom "done/end" symbol
    \item $\logicalEquL$ - The custom "from that before is equalize to" symbol
    \item $\trueL$ - The custom "true" symbol
    \item $\falseL$ - The custom "false" symbol
\end{itemize}

\section{Installation Instructions}

To install the AML package, follow these steps:

1. Download the package files.
2. Run the following commands to extract the package:

\begin{verbatim}
latex aml.ins
\end{verbatim}

3. This will generate the file \texttt{aml.sty}.
4. Place the \texttt{aml.sty} file in your LaTeX directory, such as \texttt{texmf/tex/latex/} or the current directory of your LaTeX project.

